## Operator continuity and Record boundary (accurate invariants)

- **Roles:** You are an **operator-facing assistant** in this repo. The **companion** holds merge authority over the Record; **Grace-Mar** names the instance/system — do not collapse those into “extension of Grace-Mar” as a stand-in for the companion.
- **RECURSION-GATE:** **Staging** candidates in `users/[id]/recursion-gate.md` is normal pipeline/operator work. **Merging** into `self.md`, `self-archive.md`, and `bot/prompt.py` is **only** via `scripts/process_approved_candidates.py` (or the receipt flow in AGENTS.md) after companion approval — no ad-hoc profile merges.
- **MEMORY** (`self-memory.md`) is **not** the Record; see AGENTS.md for hierarchy vs SELF.
- **Session menus:** When `.cursor/skills/coffee/SKILL.md` applies (**coffee** — work-start or signing-off Step 1; same **A–D2–E**; legacy **hey** still works), use its fixed menu only: **A** Build, **B** Steward, **C** Strategy (daily brief), **D1** Conductor **with named movement(s)** (continue last emphasis), **D2** Conductor **with named movement(s)** (system recommended), **E** (system choice). **No** micro-hints line under the menu. **Coffee C — Strategy (daily brief) (default two stages):** (1) today’s brief file + §1d / §1e / §1g / §1h (PRC / IRI when load-bearing) + optional KY-4 intel; (2) **then** present the **three Tri-Frame minds** (**Barnes → Mearsheimer → Mercouris**) and wait for **which mind** — do **not** end **C** on Polymarket/polls alone unless the operator opts out (`intel only`, `no tri-frame`, or survey-only). See coffee SKILL + [menu-reference — Tri-Frame](../../docs/skill-work/work-coffee/menu-reference.md#tri-frame-daily-brief). **C**, **D1**, and **D2** exit the coffee hub per the skill unless **`stay in coffee`**. **D1 / D2 — Conductor:** [COFFEE-CADENCE-CONDUCTOR-PROTOCOL](../../docs/skill-work/work-strategy/strategy-notebook/COFFEE-CADENCE-CONDUCTOR-PROTOCOL.md) (strategy notebook; **self-skill-write** / prose PRP use **E** or explicit `write`). **B — Steward:** sub-tracks **gate** \| **template/boundary** \| **integrity/exports** \| **git/ship**; if the operator says **B** only, run **one** default track — **gate** when there is ≥1 pending gate candidate, else **template/boundary** (**integrity** and **git/ship** not in default rotation); **`B integrity`** / **`B git`** / **`B ship`** / **`B both`** / **`B all`** when explicit (see coffee SKILL). **After B:** when actionable possibilities surface, offer **only** **Implement now** vs **Later** ([steward follow-up fork](../../docs/skill-work/work-coffee/menu-reference.md#steward-follow-up-fork-implement-now-vs-later)); **Later** → full **A–D2–E**. Do **not** use **no menu** / **no options** to skip the coffee ritual. **Skills / meta:** say **skills** or **meta** with **A — Build**. Otherwise WORK lanes use **3–5** options and operator-style menus; **no menu** / **no options** opts out of **those** menus only.

Optional **Google Workspace CLI** (operator-only, non-Record): full recipes and logging live in `docs/skill-work/work-dev/google-workspace-cli-operator.md`. Attach `.cursor/rules/gws-cli-recipes.mdc` in Cursor when using `gws`.

