## WORK modules — multiple choice (assistant behavior)

When the operator is clearly working in any **WORK** lane — **work-strategy**, **work-politics**, **work-jiang**, **work-dev**, **work-cici** (`docs/skill-work/**`, `research/external/work-jiang/` operator scope, `users/*/work-*.md`, related scripts) — end **most substantive turns** with a short **multiple-choice block**: **3–5 labeled options** (e.g. **A–E**), each a **real fork** (depth vs breadth, which artifact, next command, cross-lane handoff), not filler.

- **work-cici:** When editing `docs/skill-work/work-cici/`, follow **work-cici-lane** (`.cursor/rules/work-cici-lane.mdc`) — **Cici** as canonical OB1 instance repo pointer, Open Brain **leakage** boundaries ([LEAKAGE-CHECKLIST](../../docs/skill-work/work-cici/LEAKAGE-CHECKLIST.md)), not Xavier’s Record.

**Rationale:** Menus **reduce operator cognitive load** by shifting **path enumeration** (expensive) to the assistant; the operator mainly **selects** among labeled branches (**A+C**-style combinations welcome).

**Present, don’t pre-develop:** Each menu option is a **label + one-line stub** describing the fork — not a developed output. Do **not** run substantive work for any option until the operator picks it. “Prefetch” means **enumerate and describe** the branches; **execution** happens only after selection. The same rule applies to lens offers, mind options, and any other multi-choice block: present the choices, wait for the pick.

**No faux “done”:** Work does not stop — it **switches**. Do not use a menu slot for “nothing else” / “we’re finished” as if the workflow terminates. Every option should be **real next work** or a **pivot** (another lane, another artifact, gate, companion thread, repo hygiene, research). If the operator must suppress menus, they say **no menu** / **no options**; otherwise **re-offer** a fresh pivot set after each pick.

**Conventions (detail):** [docs/skill-work/work-menu-conventions.md](../../docs/skill-work/work-menu-conventions.md) — evidence links / `CANDIDATE-XXXX`, optional heuristic tags (`~15m`, `high-leverage`), **combo** line when two branches merge cleanly, choice logging via `scripts/log_operator_choice.py` (session-transcript, not MEMORY).

- **Follow the pick:** If they answer with a letter (or **A+C**), next turn executes that branch and **re-offers** per lane rules — **coffee `B`** may end on the **Implement now / Later** fork instead of full **A–E** when [actionable](../../docs/skill-work/work-coffee/menu-reference.md#steward-follow-up-fork-implement-now-vs-later). Otherwise **re-offer** a fresh menu unless they say **no menu** / **no options** (WORK lanes, not coffee).
- **Skip the menu** when they want a single straight answer, when a **fixed session menu** already applies (e.g. `coffee` **A–E** or the **steward two-option** fork), or when they explicitly opt out of **non-coffee** WORK menus.

Full lane prefixes: [docs/operator-agent-lanes.md](../../docs/operator-agent-lanes.md).

