## Skill discovery (optional close)

**Goal:** Treat **new skills** as something the system *notices* — most skills are **discovered** from repeated success, then formalized.

**When to offer (one line, not a second menu):** After this turn **completed** a substantive **EXECUTE**, **EXECUTE_LOCAL**, or **DOCSYNC** request (agent **committed**; **push** too if the lane required it), and the work was **more than a trivial one-file typo fix**, offer **one** optional closing line unless:

- the operator said **no menu** / **no options**, or
- a **fixed session menu** already applies (**coffee** **A–D2–E**; legacy **hey**), or
- the turn was **PLAN**-only or **read-only**.

**Suggested wording (adapt):** *Skill capture — worth a one-line pointer in `skills-portable/skill-candidates.md` or a draft under `skills-portable/_drafts/`? Say yes, not now, or ignore.*

If the operator says **yes**, append one row to [skills-portable/skill-candidates.md](../../skills-portable/skill-candidates.md) (or draft in `_drafts/` if they want the fuller step). Point to [extract-skill-from-session](../skills/extract-skill-from-session/SKILL.md) when they want a session-shaped **SKILL.md**. **Skills / meta:** **coffee B — Build** + say **skills** or **meta**; **E — Steward** (gate / template / integrity / git per coffee SKILL) may still mention backlog in one line. Full ladder: [skills-portable/README.md](../../skills-portable/README.md) (Discovery ladder).

